The Morning Brief for Tuesday, June 2, 2026 is written to `/home/bigpic/projects/bigpic-markets/morning-brief/2026-06/2026-06-02_Tue.md` (~2,600 words, calibrated to the HEAVY event load).

**The story the data tells:** a rotation day, not a risk-off day. AI hardware is ripping (MRVL +23%, HPE +27%, AVGO +6.3%, DELL doubled in 8 days) while software, cyber, and crypto sell off — all under the shadow of Alphabet's reported $80B AI-capex raise reigniting spending/ROI fears. VIX at 16 isn't confirming the bearish headlines.

**Key things I flagged:**
- **JOLTS at 10:00 ET** (6.87M est vs 6.87M prior) is the macro pivot; two Fed speakers bracket it.
- **PANW reports tonight** into an extreme RSI 84 — results not yet out, so I marked it Pending, no fabricated numbers.
- **AVGO and CRWD both report tomorrow (6/3)**, both technically extended (RSI 70 / 87) — today is effectively a pre-earnings setup.
- The **June convergence window** is building: Triple Witch positioning starts Jun 8, FOMC/witch/rebalance Jun 16–19, Russell recon Jun 26.
- Cross-sector catalysts pulled from the thesis files: Quantinuum >$14B IPO, Cameco/Orano Cigar Lake, Nov-2026 US–China expiry, Golden Dome/Northrop-Apex.

**Data integrity handling:** I honored the rules strictly — every Economic Calendar Actual was "—" so all marked Pending; PANW earnings marked not-reported; I surfaced the briefing's own quality caveats (FRED timeout → 2Y is prior close; the z-score anomalies on AVGO/MRVL/etc., noting most are genuine news-driven gaps; placeholder 0.00% on the US-index "previous close" rows). No WebSearch used; every number traces to the briefing file.

One thing worth your eye: the briefing's **US Indices "Previous Close" table shows 0.00% across the board with S&P = 7,600 (identical to futures)** — that looks like a stale/placeholder write from the collector rather than real prior-close data. I worked around it by using futures for direction, but if that recurs it may be worth a pipeline check.
